added.title: Driver's Ed
added.description: Robin is inadvertently the getaway driver for a bank robbery in the midst of his driver's ed exam.

added.title: Dreams
added.description: A glimpse inside each Titan's dream world.

added.title: Caramel Apples
added.description: Raven and Starfire clash after Starfire creates a bond with Raven's father, while Robin, Cyborg, and Beast Boy struggle to return to Earth's surface after falling into a deep cavern.

added.title: Crazy Day
added.description: It's Crazy Day again and Raven must do her best to avoid being driven crazy by the other Titans.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Nean
added.description: Raven is cursed to be nice; meanwhile, Starfire is about to marry a pot of chili.

added.title: Rad Dudes with Bad Tudes
added.description: After seeing a pair of cool dudes on rollerblades, Robin tries to be just like them.

added.title: Demon Prom
added.description: Trigon makes Raven attend her prom and she brings along the other Titans to upset him.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: TV Knight 6
added.description: Batman is forced to go to the department store with Alfred, but runs off to watch TV with Commissioner Gordon.

added.title: Kryponite
added.description: When Robin explains that knowing your weakness makes you a better superhero, Starfire journeys to find hers.

added.title: Thumb War
added.description: As the other Titans engage in an all out thumb wrestling war, Starfire tries to broker peace.

added.title: The Mustache
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's wish comes true when they suddenly turn into men.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are unwitting accomplices in a gas station robbery.

added.title: The Hero
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are determined to prove to their dad that he is their hero, at any cost!

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: The Job
added.description: Dad gets his first job as a pizza delivery guy, which rocks the very fabric of the universe.

added.title: The Remote
added.description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

added.title: The Routine
added.description: Mom and the kids depart for their hard day's work, leaving a seemingly lazy Dad half-asleep on the sofa. Mom has given him one very simple job: buy mayonnaise. However, Dad manages to turn this mundane task into an epic quest, showing that his daily routine isn't as inactive as his family imagine.

added.title: The Outside
added.description: The family goes to visit Richard's Dad. Based on his basic living standards and extended absence from Richard's life, they assume Frankie must have done a stretch in the slammer. When Frankie comes to stay with the Wattersons, they decide the way to make him comfortable is to make him uncomfortable and turn their house into a prison.

added.title: The Diet
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

added.title: The Lady
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin track a women emerging from their home, they discover her to be a member of a gang of wise-cracking elderly friends. However, as they get closer and closer to her life, they realize they may know her already.

added.title: The Slip
added.description: Richard doesn't answer the door in time and the jobsworth delivery guy will not let him have his package. His options are to pick his package up at the depot or pay for a redelivery. Richard doesn't like the sound of either option, so a battle of wills begins that can only end in the destruction of one or both of them.

added.title: The Possession
added.description: Nicole has decided it's time to throw out the family's refrigerator. This doesn't go down too well with Richard, as it's his favorite possession. When it turns out the refrigerator is also a magical storage facility for childhood emotions and memories, it makes sense that Richard is having a hard time letting go.

added.title: The Father
added.description: When Frankie attends a party at The Watterson's he realizes it's a holiday Granny Jojo made up to celebrate the day he left. Richard is feeling sad about the years he lost with Frankie so the kids try anything to cheer him up.

added.title: Venthalla
added.description: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

added.title: Duck Duck Juice
added.description: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

added.title: Cluckwork Orange
added.description: After befriending a chicken with a bad attitude at a petting zoo, Jude is followed back to school by the chicken. He defends the bad bird's behavior until he can defend it no longer.

added.title: Free Chili
added.description: When Owen hides a walkie-talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

added.title: The Date
added.description: When Chef is happy he orders pizza for the kids, this gives Owen & Jude the idea to create a fake secret admirer for Chef.

added.title: Aquarium for a Dream
added.description: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

added.title: Sharing Is Caring
added.description: Courtney refuses to share her valuable collectors item toy with her classmates.

added.title: Ant We All Just Get Along
added.description: Owen and Beth try to save an ant hill that Courtney and Leshawna want to destroy.

added.title: Germ Factory
added.description: After seeing Leshawna enjoying a sick day at home with ice cream and TV, Duncan convinces the other kids try to get sick too.

added.title: Go Fish
added.description: While on a fishing trip, the Bears get attacked by a giant legendary fish.

added.title: Teacher's Pet
added.description: The Baby Bears escape their hectic lives by attending school.

added.title: Googs
added.description: The Bears win a tour of the infamous Googs corporate headquarters.

added.title: Paperboyz
added.description: The Baby Bears get jobs as paper boys.

added.title: Bear Squad
added.description: Tabes deputizes the Bears so they can go to the city and catch a thief.

added.title: Lil' Squid
added.description: The Baby Bears build a submarine and explore the depths of an aquarium so they can bring a lost squid to its family.

added.title: I, Butler
added.description: The Bears use a robot bear to help around the house. But things get tricky when they lose control of the robot.

added.title: Family Troubles
added.description: Baby Grizz lives on the set of a sitcom in which he stars. But when a cooler kid joins the cast, Grizz feels threatened.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Falafel's Passion
added.description: Apple and Onion try to help Falafel find his passion but it looks like things might take a humiliating turn.

added.title: Hole In Roof
added.description: Suddenly the hole in the roof is no longer a laughing matter but one of a life or death.

added.title: Patty's Law
added.description: If found guilty of breaking Patty's Law, Apple and Onion face grave punishment but they have a more pressing concern; looking after their dear, sickly Falafel.

added.title: Apple & Onion's Booth
added.description: Apple and Onion must save their favorite booth at Pizza's Diner from a Texas oil tycoon.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

added.title: Face Your Fears
added.description: Apple and Onion must face their fears if they are to save French Fry from their bad advice.

added.title: Follow Your Dreams
added.description: Apple and Onion need to find a dream to follow, so that their lives don't head nowhere.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Onion must stop Apple from falling prey to his obsession, but a certain phone game is proving to be quite an obstacle.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion are faced with a philosophical question: Are they truly doing good deeds for the good of other people or is it all just for them?

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a formula for comedy that will land him a movie role.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple and Onion find a mysterious book but they better read it fast before it disappears forever.

added.title: Appleoni
added.description: The wrong person is getting credit for a new dance craze.

added.title: Falafel's in Jail
added.description: Falafel's in trouble with the law despite pleading his innocence. Apple and Onion vow to break him out.

added.title: The Music Store Thief
added.description: Instruments have been going missing from Apple and Onion's favourite music store and Chicken Nugget (who's in charge of security) doesn't want them hanging around and getting in the way.

added.title: The Fly
added.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

added.title: Out to Launch
added.description: While on a visit to Cape Canaveral, the Tennyson Trio are present for the inaugural launch of an experimental space plane. When Vilgax commandeers the ship, Ben must stop the baddie from weaponizing the shuttle before the countdown hits zero.

added.title: Battle at Biggie Box
added.description: Ben and Billy Billions go head to head over a Sumo Slammer Set sold exclusively inside the world's largest shopping center, only to find six-year-old Simon Sez has gotten it first! A battle royal ensues inside a store that seemingly has everything except an easy to find exit.

added.title: Bon Voyage
added.description: Aboard the SS Pettigrew on its final voyage, Ben must not only battle seasickness but Steam Smythe, who looks to use his mechanical creatures to sink the steamship's modern replacement and the passengers with it!

added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: Screamcatcher
added.description: When a cavity forces Ben to the dentist his day gets even worse when the malevolent magician Hex uses a nearby dream catcher to bring our hero's fears to life and transports them both to a nightmarish dreamscape.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: When Max dozes off before a double feature, Ben and Gwen are left to save the drive-in by themselves as the evil magician Hex brings the movie monster "That" to life, and unleashes him on the unsuspecting moviegoers.

added.title: Bomzobo Lives
added.description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

added.title: Animorphosis
added.description: As the Tennyson trio dig up dinosaur fossils in the Badlands, Ben is unaware that Vilgax and Dr. Amino have teamed up to steal alien DNA from within the Omnitrix, but once extracted, Vilgax double crosses his fellow villain. Ben must now join forces with the evil doctor to have a chance to defeat the big baddie, but can Dr. Amino be trusted?

added.title: Assault on Pancake Palace
added.description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

added.title: High Stress Express
added.description: During a live feed of the new transcontinental bullet train, La Grange enters the picture to outrace the train, but Ben joins in on the fun and will stop at nothing to come out on top!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Story, Bored
added.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

added.title: Hole in 10
added.description: While mini-golfing, Ben is attacked by the Ground Hawgs, a gang of Dr. Animo mutants turned bikers. When the Hawgs realize the faux mini-golf village isn't an actual town, Ben must go alien to stop them before they set their sights on the real city down the road.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Drop Beat Dad
added.description: Steven helps Sour Cream put on a show, even though Sour Cream's stepdad doesn't approve of DJs.

added.title: Greg the Babysitter
added.description: Steven learns the tale of how Greg came to work at the car wash.

added.title: Gemcation
added.description: Greg and the Gems take Steven on vacation to help him relax.

added.title: Hit the Diamond
added.description: Steven and the Gems play an old fashioned game of baseball.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Jail Break
added.description: Steven teams up with a new ally to rescue the Gems.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Sideline Dad
added.description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
added.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

added.title: Arachno Romance
added.description: After the girls feel slighted by the Professor when he gets a new girlfriend, the girls conspire to break them up.

added.title: Fashion Forward
added.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: Deb O'Nair
added.description: A classy queen of etiquette makes the Utoniums question their superhero way of life.

added.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
added.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: Powerprof.
added.description: The girls are so busy fighting crime that the Professor doesn't get to see them anymore. So he creates a superhero suit for himself. Unfortunately, he starts cramping their superhero style.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea?: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

added.title: Prime Mates/Coupe D'Etat
added.description: Prime Mates: Back when Mojo Jojo tried to take over the world with primates, there was one monkey who didn't get his due: Mopey Popo. Now, Mopey is back to try and be just as evil as Mojo intended./Coupe D'Etat: When the Professor tricks out his car, the girls realize that this K.A.R.R. is taking the Professor away from them both figuratively and literally.

added.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops, I Did It Again
added.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops, I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: It Came From the Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: Crystals Have Power
added.description: Jake takes a vow of non-violence, which is inconvenient when they're attacked by marauders from the crystal dimension.

added.title: Dad's Dungeon
added.description: Jake's Dad appears in a holographic message with a mysterious challenge for Finn and Jake.

added.title: King Worm
added.description: Finn has a particularly vivid dream, and all of Ooo is in it or does he?

added.title: Jake the Dad
added.description: Jake's a daddy, but being a father and keeping his rainicorn pups from killing themselves or each other is a lot harder than he imagined.

added.title: The Pit
added.description: Kee-Oth the Blood Demon has kidnapped Jake, taken him back to his dimension and thrown him in a pit. If Finn wants to rescue his friend, he's going to need Lady Rainicorn's help and a videotape that will reveal how to open the portal to Kee-Oth's dimension.

added.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
added.description: Finn and Jake's parents hunt an unearthly menace in the woods.

added.title: Escape from the Citadel
added.description: Finn and Jake follow the Lich of the Citadel, where Finn meets his long lost dad. But just how far does the apple fall from the tree?

added.title: Marcy & Hunson
added.description: Hunson Abadeer returns to Ooo to bond with his daughter Marceline, but will he be able to prove that he's changed his soul-sucking ways?

added.title: Varmints
added.description: Bubblegum teams up with Marceline to face a threat to her homestead's citizens.

added.title: Sky Witch
added.description: Marceline is on a top-secret mission tracking Maja the Sky Witch. When she loses the witch's trail, Marceline turns to Princess Bubblegum for help.

added.title: What Was Missing
added.description: Finn and Jake do battle with a powerful door lord.

added.title: Go With Me
added.description: Finn needs to date to the movies and must balance the contrasting advice of Jake and Marceline in wooing Princess Bubblegum so he can see that flick!

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: Dust Buddies
added.description: As punishment for making a huge mess in their house, Belson's mom makes Belson clean up, offering their usual maid service to Mary and Clarence. Embarrassed of their messy house, Mary and Clarence hurry to clean up before the maid arrives.

added.title: Hoofin' It
added.description: It's time for the annual Aberdale Greased Pig Chase and everyone's excited except Clarence. He feels so bad for poor little pig Butterscotch that he takes her place in the pig chase, running from townsfolk eager to take home the prized barrel full of hot dogs!

added.title: Lil Buddy
added.description: After playing a bit too aggressively with his Lil Buddy doll, Clarence gets timeout and his worst nightmare comes true. He misses the entire recess!

added.title: Where the Wild Chads Are
added.description: Chad takes Clarence out to the woods for some grizzly-man camping but Clarence is disappointed at the cushy set up; heaters, a hammock, even a portable TV. To make it a more rugged adventure, Clarence ditches Chad's wallet, cell phone and all their food but it may be too much wilderness for them to handle.

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Chadsgiving
added.description: Clarence is excited for Thanksgiving Dinner with Chad's parents, but Chad is worried that their unusually laid back demeanor and bizarre customs will make him look irresponsible by association.

added.title: Benson Be Gone
added.description: Mordecai sees Pops naked and goes on a quest to unsee what he has seen.

added.title: Dizzy
added.description: M and R help Pops get over his fear of public speaking.

added.title: The Best Burger in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to finish their chores before they can have burgers.

added.title: Dead at Eight
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to babysit Death's kid.

added.title: Trucker Hall of Fame
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to help Muscle Man get to the Big Rig Museum to spread his dad's hat's ashes.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: Power Tower
added.description: Muscle Man wants to win the bodybuilding competition at his gym.

added.title: Just Friends
added.description: Rigby and Eileen get called away to Don's black belt ceremony forcing Mordecai and Margaret to hang out alone.

added.title: Rigby Goes to Prom
added.description: Rigby asks Eileen to prom. But in order to get there, he has to sneak his Dad's car out of the garage and get it back in one piece.

added.title: Cast Aside the Truth
added.description: Hawkodile breaks his arm in a careless spill and lies to his friends about the accident to keep from looking bad.

added.title: Dawn of the Donut
added.description: Dr. Fox's plans to deliver donuts all over the Unikingdom are sidetracked by Unikitty's reluctance to follow instructions.

added.title: Baby Caterpillar
added.description: Unikitty takes in a radioactive caterpillar and raises it like a baby, unaware of the havoc it will wreak as a full-grown adult.

added.title: Borrowed
added.description: Richard discovers his library books have been borrowed by Master Frown and sets off on a crazed mission to return the books before they're overdue.

added.title: Pool Duel
added.description: Unikitty and the gang are having a great time at the public pool, until they try to get Puppycorn to swim in the deep end with them. Puppycorn is terrified of the deep end. Now Unikitty and the gang must get him over his fear, so he can have maximum pool fun. Meanwhile, Master Frown and Brock are hatching a plan to ruin everyone's fun, by pulling the pool's plug.

added.title: This Spells Disaster
added.description: The gang is planning a surprise for Puppycorn, so they spell things out when talking so he won't find out. Desperate to know what they're saying, Puppycorn finds a magic book that he thinks will help him learn to spell, but unbeknownst to him, it's teaching him how to cast spells! Will Puppycorn realize that knowledge is power and some secrets are kept for a reason?

added.title: Trapped in Paradise
added.description: Unikitty and the gang have crashed on a fabulous island. It's really nice and no one wants to leave until Richard convinces them that they need to return to the Kingdom and deal with their responsibilities. Unfortunately every attempt to escape the island is sabotaged. Now they must find the culprit to ensure their return home.

added.title: Volcano
added.description: A super-grumpy volcano appears in the kingdom, so Unikitty takes the gang on an epic quest to cheer it up with one of FeeBee's flowers before it erupts and destroys the kingdom.

added.title: Beach Daze
added.description: Unikitty and the gang gear up for a fun day at the beach... but when Master Frown shows up as the lifeguard to spoil their plans in the sand, Unikitty and the gang embark on a beach quest to find the legendary Perfect Spot, far away from Frown's tyrannical rule. But can they get there before Frown and claim it for their own or will their quest turn out to be a real beach bummer?

added.title: Tragic Magic
added.description: After Richard puts on an amateur magic show, Dr. Fox becomes obsessed with figuring out how his science-defying tricks are done. But as she sets about using all of her genius intellect finding experimental ways to pull off the little pup's party tricks, will she accidentally ruin the wonder of magic?

added.title: Landlord Lord
added.description: The Land Lord has threatened Master Frown and Brock with eviction unless they fix the damage they've done to their apartment. Worried, Brock invites Unikitty and the gang to help. Instead of doing what the guys want to their place, she proceeds to do what she wants. Realizing her error, she returns the apartment to its former disgusting state, but now Frown and Brock are in danger of eviction again. They must team up with Unikitty and the gang to battle the Land Lord and save their home.

added.title: Space Mission: Danger
added.description: After their spaceship explodes, Unikitty and the gang float helplessly through space. As they try to formulate a plan that will get them home safe, they flash back to how each of them is responsible for their ship being destroyed. Will they make it home, and more importantly who will be to blame if they don't.

added.title: BatKitty
added.description: The gang are at the local laundromat cleaning their clothes, when Unikitty finds Batman's uniform mixed in with her clothes.  Intoxicated by the coolness of it, Unikitty takes on the persona of Batman and begins to fight crime.  When she accidentally causes Master Frown to step up his crime game, she will need the help of her friends, dressed as Robin, to stop him.

added.title: We're Captured
added.description: Boxman captures KO, Enid and Rad, but seems a little distracted.

added.title: Parents Day
added.description: It's Parents' Day at Lakewood Plaza Turbo!

added.title: Villains' Night Out
added.description: Lord Boxman forces his way into an exclusive Villains party.

added.title: Villains' Night In
added.description: While Boxman and Venomous are out, Fink is reluctantly babysat by Darrell and Shannon.

added.title: GarQuest
added.description: Gar and KO team up for a secret mission.

added.title: Gar Trains Punching Judy
added.description: With a big fight coming up, Punching Judy turns to KO and Gar to help her prepare.

added.title: Thank You for Watching the Show
added.description: When KO finds moments of his life slipping by, he begins to suspect something weird is going on.

added.title: The More Things Change Part 2
added.description: Ben and Rook discover an underground city beneath Bellwood populated with aliens! But who is terrorizing them? (Introducing Nemetrix alien BugLizard, & Ben alien Shocksquatch, Psyphon, Fistina, Bubblehelmet, Liam.)

added.title: Washington B.C.
added.description: Ben must use the Omnitrix to transform into alien heroes to battle Dr. Amino and his transmorphed dinosaurs running rampant in Washington DC.

added.title: The Krakken
added.description: While stopped at a lakefront campsite, Ben has a chance encounter with a Loch Ness type sea monster called a Krakken, controlled by an evil poacher.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: Hunted
added.description: Three alien bounty hunters are hot on Ben's trail. But one of them is a secret agent trying to make sure the Omnitrix does not fall into evil hands.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Of Predators and Prey Part 2
added.description: While trapped in Khyber's ship, Ben learns details about the origin of the Nemetrix, and the link between Khyber, Malware, and Dr. Psychobos! (Introducing new Nemetrix alien Tyrannopede.)

added.title: A Small Problem
added.description: When Ben is not allowed on an attraction at a water park because he's too short, he decides to go alien to get even with the ride's attendant.

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Mr. Smoothy's
added.description: The Plumbers' resident geniuses, Blukic and Driba set off to find some smoothies meanwhile Ben and Rook try to stop Trombipulor from gaining the source of absolute power.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: As payment for destroying his car, Mr. Bowman orders Ben to make deliveries for him without using the Omnitrix.  (Featuring Thunderpig, new Ben alien Toepick.)

added.title: Showdown Part 2
added.description: Ben must deal with a past failure while a deranged Malware launches his final attack on Azmuth.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: Food Around the Corner
added.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Collection Infection
added.description: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: To Balderly Go
added.description: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

added.title: For the Love of Narwhal
added.description: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

added.title: Winning at Whining
added.description: Vambre's challenge to Prohyas: Don't whine for the entirety of the next mission and you can have the Magisword we get at the end.

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Changeable Terraingable
added.description: Personality conflicts between Vambre and Prohyas come to a head as the Warriors miraculously manage to ace a mission at an ever changing labyrinth.

added.title: Fixing a Flonk
added.description: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

added.title: What's My Name? Starring Vambre and Prohyas Warrior!
added.description: The Warriors go to extreme measures so folks remember their names.

added.title: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
added.description: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

added.title: Vambre's Guilty Pleasure
added.description: Vambre tries her best to keep her tough Warrior reputation intact and still go to the cutesy wootsy Piggiepie Jones stage show.

added.title: New Direction
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the best directors in the business help a kid in need of acting lessons become a star.

added.title: Chill Out
added.description: Uncle Grandpa takes a kid to the North Pole for an epic snowball battle.

added.title: Mr. Gus Moves Out
added.description: When a fed-up Mr. Gus moves out of the RV, Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve work together to get him back.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Fleas Help Me
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang help their K9 pal, Charlie Burgers, get rid of his flea infestation.

added.title: Are You Talking to Tree?
added.description: When the tree inside the RV begins talking to Uncle Grandpa, he must convince the gang that he's not going crazy.

added.title: Nacho Cheese
added.description: Pizza Steve's father comes to visit the gang and almost immediately gets on their nerves with his over the top antics. Pizza Steve must get rid of his dad, and prove to himself that he doesn't need to live in his father's shadow any longer.

added.title: Afraid of the Dark
added.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

added.title: Bad Morning
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa wakes up on the wrong side of the bed, he changes into a grumpy grump and it's up to the rest of the gang to reverse his bad day.

added.title: 1992 Called
added.description: Uncle Grandpa travels back to the year 1492 to retrieve a pair of pants.

added.title: Bezt Frends
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to extreme measures to surpass Pizza Steve as Pizza Steve's best friend.

added.title: Aunt Grandma
added.description: The gang must stop a nefarious imposter from rendering Uncle Grandpa obsolete.

added.title: Ballin'
added.description: Uncle Grandpa, Pizza Steve, and Mr. Gus must win a basketball game against a super awesome b-ball crew in order to keep the RV.

added.title: Barehanded
added.description: When Green Lantern leaves his ring in an intergalactic restroom after washing his hands, he discovers it's gone, leading him on a wild chase for the aliens who might have taken it.

added.title: Captain Bamboozle
added.description: Mr. Mxyzptlk decides to create some mischief by endowing Shazam's well-meaning Uncle Dudley with superpowers bigger than anyone in the league.

added.title: Keeping Up with the Kryptonians
added.description: Mr. Mxyzptlk shows Supergirl and Superman that their innate goodness might not be so pure when he takes them to a parallel world where their counterparts are impossibly aggressive and spoiled.

added.title: Unleashed
added.description: While the Justice League is away on a mission, Plastic Man is not only left in charge of the Watchtower, but also Superman's dog, Krypto.

added.title: She Wore Red Velvet
added.description: When Booster and the JLA come under attack by a mysterious and unrelenting new villainess known as Red Velvet, Booster comes to realize she's actually the fiance he left at the altar in the future.

added.title: Bucket List
added.description: The Titans give Starfire a bucket list of activities to accomplish.

added.title: La Posesion
added.description: Richard Watterson parece estar sobrenaturalmente unido a su viejo refrigerador.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Toddler Titans...Yay!
added.description: Control Freak thinks the Titans' humor is too juvenile for their time-slot, so he ages them down to a preschool show.

added.title: Mision Gar
added.description: El Sr. Gar y KO hacen equipo para una misión secreta.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Burrito
added.description: A Pardo le gustan los burritos. Mucho. Tanto que cuando un restaurant elabora un Burrito tamaño oso, Pardo se obliga a comer semejante obra de arte majestuosa. Lleva el burrito consigo a todas partes y lo convierte en una parte nueva y cada vez más olorosa de su vida.

added.title: Chaqueta De Mezclilla
added.description: Los Osos encuentran una chaqueta de jean deslumbrante en un contenedor de basura. Es una de las cosas más fabulosas que jamás hayan visto, y parece convertir a aquel que la use en una persona extremadamente afortunada. Pero cuando los Osos discuten para ver quién queda a cargo de la chaqueta, empiezan a pensar que su bendición de denim se convirtió en una maldición.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: ¿Viste cuando tienes un amigo que no entiende una indirecta? Ese es Charlie, Pie Grande. Los Osos lo conocen cuando Charlie se inscribe en un sitio web para personas que comparten su casa y se instala un fin de semana con los Osos. Charlie es el peor invitado posible para los Osos y prácticamente destruye la casa.

added.title: Hora De Ser Villano
added.description: Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para evitar un desastre en la represa Hoover, pero cuando Tim Buktu, el heroico tipo rudo, se precipita para ayudar, Ben debe descubrir si Tim es su amigo...o su enemigo.

added.title: Conduciendo A La Locura
added.description: Cuando la Chatarra se rompe en un parque de casas rodantes, Ben descubre que se encuentran en la última etapa del Cali 10 Hundred-una carrera de autos épica todo terreno-en la que LaGrange, el piloto demente, ha regresado en busca de venganza contra aquellos que lo descalificaron hace años.

added.title: Manana Es Hoy
added.description: Cuando Max arrastra a los niños a ver una "Casa del futuro" obsoleta construida por su ídolo de la infancia, Ben descubre que Vapor Smythe está ocupado excavando el lugar en busca de un dispositivo poderoso que le permitirá crear armas devastadoras para su guerra en progreso. Solo la devoción de Max por su ídolo de la infancia y la fe de Ben en los sueños puede salvar el mañana...ihoy mismo!

added.title: Lectura, Que Aburrido
added.description: Durante una firma de libros en un castillo medieval, Ben debe impedir que Hex se apodere de un grimorio que puede fusionar a su lector con bestias míticas...iy así crear híbridos monstruosos!

added.title: Hoyo En 10
added.description: Mientras Ben juega al minigolf, lo atacan los Ground Hawgs, una pandilla de mutantes convertidos en ciclistas del Doctor Ánimo. Pero cuando los Hawgs se dan cuenta de que la falsa aldea de minigolf no es un lugar real, Ben debe transformarse en alienígena para detenerlos antes de que elijan la ciudad verdadera que está a pocos metros de allí como su blanco.

added.title: Falafel en la Carcel
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben sacar a Falafel de la cárcel por un delito que no cometió.

added.title: Dia de padres
added.description: It's Parents' Day at Lakewood Plaza Turbo!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La Mosca
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben deshacerse de una mosca que se metió en su apartamento o enfrentarse al desalojo.

added.title: Manzallin
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín quieren llevarse el crédito de haber creado una nueva moda de baile.

added.title: Rio de Oro
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla intentan terminar un cuento antes de que el libro desaparezca para siempre.

added.title: El Ladron de Musica
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín tienen que defender la tienda de música del robo de instrumentos para conseguir una llave de la tienda.

added.title: La Dama
added.description: Los niños descubren que Papá se ha vestido como una mujer para conocer amigos.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Vecino
added.description: Gumball y Darwin intentan averiguar el nombre de su vecino, el tipo de los cuernos. Pero, por accidente, develan su identidad falsa de testigo protegido.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Recibo
added.description: Papá pierde un paquete y se ve envuelto en una pelea cada vez mayor con el repartidor.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Los Verdaderos Orijanes
added.description: Robin trata de contar la verdadera historia del origen de los Jóvenes Titanes.

added.title: Hoyuelitos
added.description: Raven compite en un certamen de belleza, creyendo que es la forma de reconectarse con su padre.

added.title: Baile Demoniaco
added.description: Trigon invita a Raven a su baile de graduación, y ella lleva a los demás Titanes para molestarlo.

added.title: Duelo en la Piscina
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla se están divirtiendo mucho en la piscina pública, hasta que intentan que Perricornio nade en la parte profunda con ellos. A Perricornio le da muchísimo miedo ir a lo más profundo. Ahora Unikitty y la banda deben ayudarlo a superar su miedo para que se divierta al máximo en la piscina. Mientras tanto, Master Frown y Brock están tramando un plan para arruinar la diversión de todos: quitar el tapón de la piscina. Ahora Perricornio debe dominar su miedo para detener a los que quieren estropear la diversión.

added.title: Despeguemos
added.description: De excursión en Cabo Cañaveral, el trío Tennyson presencia el lanzamiento inaugural de una nave espacial experimental, pero cuando Vilgax comanda la nave, Ben debe impedir que el villano use el transbordador como arma antes de que la cuenta regresiva llegue a cero.

added.title: Batalla en El Biggie Box
added.description: Ben y Billy Billions se enfrentan por un set de sumo exclusivo que se vende únicamente en el centro comercial más grande del mundo, isolo para descubrir que Simon Sez, de apenas seis años, lo compró primero! Así se desata una batalla dentro de una tienda que parece tenerlo todo excepto una salida fácil de encontrar.

added.title: Buen Viaje
added.description: Abordo del SS Pettigrew en su último viaje, Ben debe luchar no solo contra el mareo sino también contra Vapor Smythe, que se propone usar a sus criaturas mecánicas para hundir el barco moderno que remplaza al vapor... iy a sus pasajeros!

added.title: Letras Desastrosas
added.description: La pandilla está planeando una sorpresa para Puppycorn, así que deletrean las cosas cuando hablan para que él no se entere. Desesperado por saber lo que dicen, Puppycorn encuentra un libro mágico que cree que lo ayudará a aprender a deletrear, ipero sin saberlo, el libro le enseña a lanzar hechizos! ¿Se dará cuenta Puppycorn de que el conocimiento es poder, y de que algunos secretos se guardan por una razón?

added.title: Desastre en Mascota
added.description: Frustrado su intento de conseguir una foto con cada mascota de vidriera, Ben y Gwen se escabullen de noche para tomarse su foto con el tótem del oso de madera... iy descubren que él y las demás mascotas cobraron vida!

added.title: Atrapagritos
added.description: Cuando una caries obliga a Ben a ir al dentista, su día empeora aún más cuando el malévolo mago Hex usa un atrapasueños para materializar los miedos de nuestro héroe y los transporta con él a un lugar pesadillesco.

added.title: Presentando a La Creatura
added.description: Cuando Max se queda dormido antes de una doble función, Ben y Gwen se ven obligados a salvar el autocine solos. Ocurre que el malvado mago Hex da vida al monstruo de una película, que aterroriza a los espectadores.

added.title: Bombazobo Vive
added.description: Durante un viaje de rutina al DMV, Max toma un examen de manejo para renovar su licencia. Pero cuando Zombozo, disfrazado, se apropia del papel del instructor, Ben se convierte en alienígena para detener al malvado y salvar el viaje familiar.

added.title: Animorfosis
added.description: El trío Tennyson excava fósiles de dinosaurio, pero Ben no sabe que Vilgax y el Dr. Animal se complotaron para robar ADN alien del Omnitrix, pero, una vez extraído el ADN, Vilgax traiciona a su cómplice. Ahora Ben debe aliarse con el malvado doctor si quiere tener la oportunidad de derrotar al gran villano. Pero ¿puede confiar en el Dr. Animal?

added.title: Ataque en el Palacio de los Panqueques
added.description: Cuando Gwen se inscribe en un concurso de comer panqueques en el mundialmente famoso Palacio de los Panqueques, Ben encuentra a los Bugg Bros. y debe detenerlos antes de que puedan obtener una provisión infinita del elemento que les da vida a sus creaciones: los panqueques del Palacio del Panqueque.

added.title: Expreso De Gran Estres
added.description: Durante una transmisión en vivo del nuevo tren bala transcontinental, La Grange se cuela para ganarle al tren. Pero Ben se suma a la diversión, iy no se detendrá ante nada para salir victorioso!

added.title: Atrapados en el paraiso
added.description: Unikitty y la banda aterrizaron de emergencia en una isla fabulosa. Todo es muy bonito y nadie quiere irse hasta que Richard los convence de que tienen que volver al Reino y asumir sus responsabilidades. Por desgracia, alguien sabotea cada intento de escapar de la isla. Ahora deben encontrar al culpable para asegurar su regreso a casa.

added.title: Volcan
added.description: Un volcán súper gruñón aparece en el reino. Por eso, Unikitty lleva a la banda a una misión épica para alegrarlo con una de las flores de FeeBee antes de que entre en erupción y destruya el reino. Pero FeeBee no tiene ganas de compartir sus queridas flores, y trata de sabotear la misión. ¿Será capaz Unikitty de convencerla de los beneficios de compartir para salvar el reino de la destrucción?

added.title: Nos Capturaron
added.description: Box-man captura a K.O., Enid y Rad, pero parece un poco distraído.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Dia de Playa
added.description: Unikitty y la pandilla se preparan para un día divertido en la playa, pero cuando Master Frown aparece como socorrista para arruinar sus planes en la arena, Unikitty y la pandilla se embarcan en una búsqueda para encontrar el legendario lugar perfecto, lejos del dominio tiránico de Frown. Pero ¿podrán llegar allí antes de que Frown lo reclame para él o su búsqueda se convertirá en un verdadero fastidio playero?

added.title: Magia Tragica
added.description: Cuando Richard monta un espectáculo de magia amateur, la Dra. Fox se obsesiona por descubrir cómo se hacen esos trucos que desafían la ciencia. Pero mientras se propone usar todo su intelecto para encontrar formas experimentales de hacer los trucos que vio en la fiesta del cachorro, ¿acaso arruinará accidentalmente el asombro de la magia?

added.title: Senor Casero
added.description: El propietario amenazó a Master Frown y a Brock con desalojarlos a menos que arreglen el daño que le hicieron a su apartamento. Preocupado, Brock invita a Unikitty y a la pandilla para que los ayuden. En lugar de hacer lo que los chicos quieren en su casa, Unikitty procede a hacer lo que ella quiere. Al darse cuenta de su error, devuelve el apartamento a su antiguo estado asqueroso, pero ahora Frown y Brock están en peligro de desalojo de nuevo. Deben aliarse a Unikitty y la banda para luchar contra el malvado casero y salvar su hogar.

added.title: Mision Espacial Peligrosa
added.description: Después de la explosión de su nave espacial, Unikitty y la banda flotan indefensos por el espacio. Mientras tratan de formular un plan que los lleve a casa a salvo, vuelven a ver qué parte de la responsabilidad por la destrucción de su nave tiene cada uno. ¿Lograrán volver a casa? Y lo que es más importante, ¿quién tendrá la culpa si no lo hacen?

added.title: La noche de fiesta de los villanos
added.description: Lord Box-man entra a la fuerza en una fiesta exclusiva para villanos.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Bati-Kitty
added.description: La banda está lavando ropa en la lavandería local, cuando Unikitty encuentra el uniforme de Batman mezclado con su ropa. Embriagada al ver lo genial que es el disfraz, Unikitty adopta la personalidad de Batman y comienza a luchar contra el crimen. Cuando accidentalmente hace que Master Frown intensifique su actividad delictiva, Unikitty necesitará la ayuda de sus amigos, vestidos todos como Robin, para detenerlo.

added.title: La noche de los villanos en casa
added.description: Mientras Box-man y Venomous no están, Darrell y Shannon cuidan a Fink, aunque él no quiera.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Sigue Tus Suenos
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín necesitan encontrar un sueño que perseguir para que sus vidas tengan un rumbo.

added.title: Salchichas y Dulce Golpe
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben superar sus obsesiones por las salchichas y los videojuegos.

added.title: Enfrenta Tus Miedos
added.description: Atrapados en una tienda de mascotas, Manzana y Cebollín deben enfrentarse a sus miedos para poder evitar que Papa Frita se enfrente a los suyos.

added.title: La Formula de Manzana
added.description: Manzana necesita encontrar una fórmula divertida que le permita conseguir un papel cómico en una película.

added.title: Ego - Egoista
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla tienen que demostrar que no son egoístas cuando hacen sus buenas acciones.

removed.description: Axel and the team must intervene when Zoe's not-so-friendly bowling competition with Cleo LeBall gets interrupted by Madcap, Porcupunk, and their new cohort, the mischievously magnetic Dynamo.

removed.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

removed.description: Colosal se vuelve enorme para destruir a un monstruo altísimo, pero cuando se rehúsa a volver a su tamaño normal, el reino se enfrenta a un nuevo terror… el apetito insaciable de Colosal.

removed.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
removed.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

removed.description: Mordecai pocket dials an embarrassing message on Margaret's phone.

removed.description: Pursued by a magma monster, Cole, Princess Vania, Wu & the Lowly arrive at a mysterious temple deep in Shintaro Mountain, a temple which was once a training ground for Earth Elementals including Cole's own mother, Lilly!

removed.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.
